What isn’t working from there? They have steps all the way from installation, to full examples of Robot integration. I’m not sure which few lines you’re referencing, but basically, yes. Their examples are pretty close to exactly what you need to do it.

Here’s our vision subsystem, we’re using PhotonVision on a Limelight with a USB camera attached. Limelight does the high goal target, USB camera tracks cargo on the ground.

Hopefully that helps.

So I have a basic calibration on the dashboard and this is all the code I have basically a slightly edited copy and paste from the Photon documentation. I read through your code but most of it didn’t really atone to our robot since all I recognized was you initiating a more advanced type of vision tracking. However I do believe I recognized my issue. Firstly, I don’t have the pipeline selected and secondly, I do not have the vision tracking lights on. I was wondering for the USB Camera LEDs do I plug them into the RPi or the RIO. If its the RPi which GPIO pins?
